# Second Brain — Vault Schema

This vault is a personal knowledge base managed by AI agent skills (Claude Code or OpenAI Codex).

> **Codex note**: this `AGENTS.md` is the Codex-read twin of `CLAUDE.md` — same body, different
> filename. Run `$second-brain-setup` (or `/second-brain-setup` under Claude Code) to generate
> both, or copy this file to `AGENTS.md` and fill in `[INTERESTS]` manually. Codex also reads
> MCP servers from `~/.codex/config.toml`, not from this file (see the `[CRAFT]` section below).

## Folder Rules

- `raw/` — All source content. NEVER modified by AI skills. Append-only.
  - `raw/craft/` — Notes imported from Craft via the second-brain-import-craft skill
  - `raw/pdf/` — Text extracted from PDFs via the second-brain-import-pdf skill
  - `raw/images/` — Visual descriptions of images imported via the second-brain-import-file skill
  - `raw/.ingest-manifest.json` — Machine-managed ingestion state. Do not edit.
- `wiki/` — AI-organised knowledge. Written ONLY by the second-brain-ingest skill.
  - One markdown file per topic, cross-linked with [[wikilinks]]
  - `wiki/INDEX.md` — Master topic index, rebuilt on every ingest
- `outputs/` — Query answers and lint reports. Written by query and lint skills.
  - `YYYY-MM-DD_query-<slug>.md` — Query output files
  - `YYYY-MM-DD_lint.md` — Lint report files

## AI Behaviour Rules

- Never modify files in `raw/`
- Never delete files in `wiki/`
- Every wiki article must start with a summary paragraph
- Every wiki article must end with a Sources footer listing contributing raw files
- Use [[topic-name]] wikilink syntax (without .md extension) for cross-references
- When synthesising wiki content, prioritise topics listed under [INTERESTS] below

## Configuration

### [INTERESTS]
<!-- Replace these with your own areas of interest.
     The ingest skill uses these to prioritise and organise wiki articles.
     Be specific — name the domain, role, or project so the model knows what matters. -->

- Topic One — brief description of what this covers and why it matters to you
- Topic Two — brief description of what this covers and why it matters to you
- Topic Three — brief description of what this covers and why it matters to you

### [CRAFT] (optional — delete this section if you don't use Craft)
<!--
  To enable Craft import:
  1. Add the Craft MCP server to your agent:
       - Claude Code: Settings → MCP Servers.
       - Codex: add a [mcp_servers.craft] entry to ~/.codex/config.toml pointing at the MCP URL.
  2. Fill in your space name and MCP URL below.
  3. Set CRAFT_ENABLED=1 in your .env file to show the import card in the dashboard.
-->
Space: YourSpaceName
MCP URL: https://mcp.craft.do/links/YOUR_TOKEN/mcp
Mode: targeted — always specify Folder/DocumentName at invocation (e.g. "AI/Meeting notes")
Known folders: Folder1, Folder2, Folder3
